'''Jamie Jaleel Jeremy Leweling''' (born 26 February 2001) is a German professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]], [[right winger]], or [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{German football updater|Stuttgart}} club [[VfB Stuttgart]] and the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]].<ref name="WF" >{{WorldFootball.net|jamie-leweling}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Greuther Fürth===
Leweling made his professional debut for [[SpVgg Greuther Fürth|Greuther Fürth]] in the [[2. Bundesliga]] on 28 July 2019, coming on as a substitute in the 85th minute for [[Tobias Mohr]] in 2–0 home loss against [[FC Erzgebirge Aue|Erzgebirge Aue]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma8935922/lineup/ |title=SpVgg Greuther Fürth – Erzgebirge Aue 0:2 (2. Bundesliga 2019/2020, 1. Round) |website=WorldFootball|publisher=Heim: Spiel|date=28 July 2019 |access-date=28 July 2019}}</ref> Later that year, on 7 December, he recorded his first goal and assist for the club in a 3–1 victory against [[VfL Bochum|Bochum]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.kicker.de/fuerth-gegen-bochum-2019-bundesliga-4589088/spielinfo |title=SpVgg Greuther Fürth 3–1 VfL Bochum|magazine=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|publisher=Olympia-Vertlag GmbH|language=de |date=7 December 2019 }}</ref>

Following the club's promotion to the [[Bundesliga]], he scored five goals during the [[2021–22 Bundesliga|2021–22 season]], opening his account with a goal against [[VfB Stuttgart]] in a 5–1 loss in the season's opening match.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/who-is-vfb-stuttgart-s-latest-germany-hopeful-jamie-leweling-29213 |title=Jamie Leweling: Who is the VfB Stuttgart forward and Germany debutant? |publisher=Bundesliga |date=15 October 2024 }}</ref>

===Union Berlin===
On 17 May 2022, it was confirmed that Leweling would join Bundesliga club [[1. FC Union Berlin|Union Berlin]] for the 2022–23 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=1. FC Union Berlin|url=https://www.fc-union-berlin.de/en/union-live/latest-news/professional/Union-sign-Fuerth-s-Jamie-Leweling-964l/|title=Union signs Fürth's Jamie Leweling|date=17 May 2022|access-date=22 July 2022}}</ref> On 21 January 2023, he scored his first goal for the club in a 3–1 league victory against [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|Hoffenheim]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fc-union-berlin.de/de/fussball/profis/spielplan/detail/-1-FC-Union-Berlin-TSG-Hoffenheim-16544P/|url-status=dead|title=Union schlägt Hoffenheim mit 3:1|publisher=1. FC Union Berlin |language=de |date=21 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230131125029/https://www.fc-union-berlin.de/de/fussball/profis/spielplan/detail/-1-FC-Union-Berlin-TSG-Hoffenheim-16544P/|archive-date=31 January 2023}}</ref>

===VfB Stuttgart===
On 13 July 2023, Leweling moved to [[VfB Stuttgart]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=VfB Stuttgart|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2324/vfb-stuttgart-verpflichtet-jamie-leweling/|title=Jamie Leweling joins VfB|date=13 July 2023|access-date=13 July 2023}}</ref> On 27 January 2024, he scored his first goal in a 5–2 victory against [[RB Leipzig]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.sportschau.de/regional/swr/swr-beim-vfb-stuttgart-lacht-jetzt-niemand-mehr-ueber-jamie-leweling-100.html|url-status=dead|title=Beim VfB Stuttgart lacht jetzt niemand mehr über Jamie Leweling|magazine=[[Sportschau]]|language=de|date=29 January 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240129173209/https://www.sportschau.de/regional/swr/swr-beim-vfb-stuttgart-lacht-jetzt-niemand-mehr-ueber-jamie-leweling-100.html|archive-date=29 January 2024}}</ref> On 19 May 2024, Leweling signed for Stuttgart permanently with a contract until June 2028.<ref>{{cite web|website=VfB Stuttgart|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2324/verpflichtung-jamie-leweling/|title=VfB make Leweling signing permanent|date=19 May 2024|access-date=19 May 2024}}</ref> In December 2024, Leweling extended his contract with VfB Stuttgart until June 2029.<ref>{{cite web|website=VfB Stuttgart|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2425/vorzeitige-vertragsverlaengerung-jamie-leweling-/|title=Jamie Leweling extends long-term VfB deal|date=17 December 2024|access-date=17 December 2024}}</ref> On 21 January 2025, he scored his first [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] brace in a 3–1 away victory against [[ŠK Slovan Bratislava|Slovan Bratislava]].<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.sportschau.de/fussball/championsleague/xx,bratislava-stuttgart-champions-league-100.html |title=Stuttgarts Leweling mit Traumtag gegen Bratislava|magazine=Sportschau |language=de |date=21 January 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Germany, Leweling is of German, French, and Ghanaian descent.<ref name="Ghana" /> His mother is German,<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2024-11-10 |author=Alexander Kaindl |date=2024-10-16 |title=Jamie Leweling: Der neue Liebling, den der DFB fast verloren hätte |url=https://www.fr.de/sport/fussball/jamie-leweling-der-neue-liebling-den-der-dfb-fast-verloren-haette-93355751.html |website=Frankfurter Rundschau}}<!-- auto-translated from German by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> his father is Ghanaian.<ref name="union">{{cite web|access-date=2022-07-01 |date=2022-05-17 |title=Jamie Leweling wechselt an die Alte Försterei |url=https://www.fc-union-berlin.de/de/union-live/news/profis/Jamie-Leweling-wechselt-an-die-Alte-Foersterei-20586V/ |website=fc-union-berlin.de}}<!-- auto-translated from German by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> In addition to German, Leweling holds both Ghanaian and French citizenships.<ref name="Ghana">{{Cite web|url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/german-born-forward-jamie-leweling-handed-maiden-black-stars-call-up|url-status=dead|title=German-born forward Jamie Leweling handed maiden Black Stars call-up|date=30 October 2020|website=Ghana Soccernet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106165235/https://ghanasoccernet.com/german-born-forward-jamie-leweling-handed-maiden-black-stars-call-up|archive-date=6 November 2020}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]] in October 2020, but he never made an appearance.<ref name="Ghana"/>

In October 2024, Leweling was selected by coach [[Julian Nagelsmann]] to represent [[Germany national football team|Germany]], replacing injured [[Jamal Musiala]], for the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A|UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/neues/laenderspiele/2024/jamie-leweling-im-dfb-aufgebot/|url-status=dead|title=Jamie Leweling im DFB-Aufgebot |publisher=VfB Stuttgart |language=de |date=4 October 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241007035913/https://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/neues/laenderspiele/2024/jamie-leweling-im-dfb-aufgebot/|archive-date=7 October 2024}}</ref> On 14 October, he made his debut whilst scoring the only goal in 1–0 victory against the latter opponent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/nations-league-deutschland-holland-1-0-das-dolle-ding-von-jamie-leweling-670d5d573e343a712d386157 |title=Traumtor von Überraschungs-Debütant sichert uns den Sieg: Das dolle Ding von Leweling|website=[[Bild]]|publisher=[[Axel Springer SE]]|language=de |date=14 October 2024 }}</ref>

On 21 May 2026, he was selected in Germany’s 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/news/bundestrainer-nagelsmann-gibt-wm-kader-bekannt|title=Bundestrainer Nagelsmann gibt WM-Kader bekannt|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|language=de|date=21 May 2026|access-date=21 May 2026}}</ref>

